18/11/21, 09:56 - +91 70609 05001: Dear class members, your LAB TEST for SYSTEM MODELING AND DESIGN LAB will be conducted on 18.11.2021 (Thursday) over MS team, starting at 1:00 PM. The lab test will include a Quiz, implementation of the experiment, viva-voice, and submission of your record file. 

  

Your record file must include a single word document of all the experiments (total 10) performed in the lab with sections as follows: 

Objective of the experiment

Software used

Theory

MATLAB code

Results and discussion

Conclusion

In software used, mention your operating version of MATLAB ( Ex. MATLAB 2016a). For theory section, write the context or background of your experiment in brief. You can add any mathematical formula or figures if required. In the results and discussion section, you have to paste a snapshot of the result figures corresponding to each experiment and analyze the important findings of your obtained results. The conclusion section must include a brief summary of what was done in the experiment and findings for the same. 

  

Note: Students having any kind of issues regarding lab test can contact Sir through his official email id.

24. कैल्शियम सल्फेट — CaSO₄
25. अमोनियम सल्फेट — (NH₄)₂SO₄
26. नाइट्रेट पोटेशियम—KNO₃
आम रसायनों के व्यावसायिक एवं रासायनिक नाम
व्यावसायिक नाम — IAPUC नाम — अणु सूत्र
27. चाक — कैल्सियम कार्बोनेट — CaCO₃
28. अंगूर का सत — ग्लूकोज — C6H₁₂O6
एल्कोहल — एथिल 29. एल्कोहल — C₂H5OH
30. कास्टिक पोटाश — पोटेशियम हाईड्राक्साईड — KOH
31. खाने का सोडा — सोडियम बाईकार्बोनेट — NaHCO₃
32. चूना — कैल्सियम आक्साईड — CaO
33. जिप्सम — कैल्सियम सल्फेट — CaSO₄.2H₂O
34. टी.एन.टी. — ट्राई नाईट्रो टालीन — C6H₂CH₃(NO₂)₃
35. धोने का सोडा — सोडियम कार्बोनेट — Na₂CO₃
36. नीला थोथा — कॉपर सल्फेट — CuSO₄
37. नौसादर — अमोनियम क्लोराईड — NH₄Cl
38. फिटकरी — पोटैसियम एलुमिनियम सल्फेट — K₂SO₄Al₂(SO₄)₃.24H₂O
39. बुझा चूना — कैल्सियम हाईड्राक्साईड — Ca(OH)₂
40. मंड — स्टार्च — C6H10O5
41. लाफिंग गैस — नाइट्रस आक्साईड — N₂O
42. लाल दवा — पोटैसियम परमैगनेट — KMnO₄
43. लाल सिंदूर — लैड परआक्साईड — Pb₃O₄
44. शुष्क बर्फ — ठोस कार्बन-डाई-आक्साईड — CO₂
45. शोरा — पोटैसियम नाइट्रेट — KNO₃
46. सिरका — एसिटिक एसिड का तनु घोल — CH₃COOH
47. सुहागा — बोरेक्स — Na₂B₄O7.10H₂O
48. स्प्रिट — मैथिल एल्कोहल — CH₃OH
49. स्लेट — सिलिका एलुमिनियम आक्साईड — Al₂O₃2SiO₂.2H₂O
50.हरा कसीस — फैरिक सल्फेट — Fe₂(SO₄)

 *भौतिक राशि Physical quantities अन्य भौतिक राशियों से संबंध* 

1. क्षेत्रफल Area लंबाई × चौड़ाई

2. आयतन Volume लंबाई× चौड़ाई×ऊंचाई

3. द्रव्यमान घनत्व Density द्रव्यमान/आय
4. आवृत्ति Frequency 1/आवर्तकाल

5. वेग Velocity विस्थापन/समय

6. चाल Speed दूरी/समय

7. त्वरण Acceleration वेग/समय

8. बल Force द्रव्यमान × त्वरण

9. आवेग Impulse बल × समय

10. कार्य Work बल × दूरी

11. ऊर्जा Energy बल × दूरी

12. शक्ति Power कार्य/समय

13. संवेग Momentum द्रव्यमान × वेग

14. दाब Pressure बल/क्षेत्रफल

15. प्रतिबल Stress बल/क्षेत्रफल

16. विकृति Strain विमा में परिवर्तन/मूल विमा

17. प्रत्यास्थता गुणांक Coefficient of elasticity प्रतिबल/विकृति

18. पृष्ठ तनाव Surface tension बल/लंबाई

19. पृष्ठ ऊर्जा Surface energy ऊर्जा/क्षेत्रफल

20. वेग प्रवणता Velocity gradient वेग/दूरी

21. दाब प्रवणता Pressure gradient दाब/दूरी

22. श्यानता गुणांक Coefficient of viscosity बल/(क्षेत्रफल× वेग प्रवणता)

23. कोण Angel चाप/त्रिज्या

24. त्रिकोणमितीय अनुपात Trigonometric ratio लंबाई/लंबाई

25. कोणीय वेग Angular velocity कोण/समय

26. कोणीय त्वरण Angular acelleration कोणीय वेग/समय

27. कोणीय संवेग Angular momentum जड़त्व आघूर्ण × कोणीय वेग

28. जड़त्व आघूर्ण Moment of inertia द्रव्यमान× (परिभ्रमण त्रिज्या)2

29. बल आघूर्ण Torque बल × दूरी

30. कोणीय आवृत्ति Angular frequency 2π × आवृत्ति

31. गुरुत्वीय सार्वत्रिक नियतांक Universal constant of gravity बल× (दूरी)2/(द्रव्यमान)2

32. प्लांक नियतांक Plank’s constant ऊर्जा/आवृत्ति

33. विशिष्ट उष्मा Specific heat उष्मीय ऊर्जा/(द्रव्यमान× ताप)

34. उष्मा धारिता Heat capacity ऊष्मीय ऊर्जा/ताप

35. बोल्टजमान नियतांक Boltzmann’s constant ऊर्जा/ताप

36. स्टीफन नियतांक Stefan’s constant (ऊर्जा/क्षेत्रफल× समय)/(ताप)4

37. गैस नियतांक Gas constant (दाब× आयतन)/(मोल× ताप )

38. आवेश Charge विद्युत धारा × समय

39. विभवातंर Potential difference कार्य/आवेश

40. प्रतिरोध Resistance विभवांतर/विद्युत धारा

41. धारिता Capacity आवेश/विभवांतर

42. विद्युत क्षेत्र Electric field वैद्युत बल/आवेश

43. चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र Magnetic field बल/(विद्युत धारा× लंबाई)

44. चुम्बकीय फ्लक्स Magnetic flux चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र × लंबाई

45. प्रेरकत्व Inductance चुम्बकीय फ्लक्स/विद्युत धारा

46. वीन नियतांक Wein’s constant तरंगदैर्ध्य ×ताप

47. चालकता Conductivity 1/प्रतिरोध

48. एंट्रॅापी Entropy ऊष्मीय ऊर्जा / ताप

49. गुप्त उष्मा Latent heat उष्मीय ऊर्जा / द्रव्यमान

50. तापीय प्रसार गुणांक Coefficient of thermal expansion विमा में परिवर्तन / (मूल विमा × ताप )

nbsp51. आयतन प्रत्यास्थता गुणांक Bulk modulus ( आयतन × दाब में परिवर्तन )/आयतन में परिवर्तन

52. वैद्युत प्रतिरोधकता Electric resistance ( प्रतिरोध × क्षेत्रफल )/ लंबाई

53. वैद्युत द्विध्रुव आघूर्ण Electric dipole moment बल आघूर्ण / विद्युत क्षेत्र

54. चुम्बकीय द्विध्रुव आघूर्ण Magnetic dipole moment बल आघूर्ण / चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र

55. चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र प्रबलता चुम्बकीय आघूर्ण / आयतन

56. अपवर्तनांक Refractive index निर्वात में प्रकाश की चाल/माध्यम में प्रकाश की चाल

57. तरंग संख्या Wave number 2π / तरंगदैर्ध्य

58. विकिरण शक्ति Radiant power उत्सर्जित ऊर्जा / समय

59. विकिरण तीव्रता Radiant intensity विकिरण शक्ति / घन कोण

60. हबल नियतांक Hubble constant पश्च सरण चाल /दूरी

 जीव विज्ञान के प्रश्न- 

1.: - मांसपेशियों में किस अम्ल के एकत्रित होने से थकावट आती है?
Ans : - लैक्टिक अम्ल
2.: - अंगूर में कौन-सा अम्ल पाया जाता है?
Ans : - टार्टरिक अम्ल
3.: - कैंसर सम्बन्धी रोगों का अध्ययन कहलाता है
Ans : - -ऑरगेनोलॉजी
4.: - मानव शरीर में सबसे लम्बी कोशिका कौन-सी होती है?
Ans : - तंत्रिका कोशिका
5.: - दाँत मुख्य रूप से किस पदार्थ के बने होते हैं?
Ans : - डेंटाइन के
6.: - किस जंतु की आकृति पैर की चप्पल के समान होती है?
Ans : - पैरामीशियम

Ans : - एक भी नहीं

Ans : - विटामिन A
9.: - निम्न में से किस पदार्थ में प्रोटीन नहीं पाया जाता है?
Ans : - चावल

Ans : - 1350

Ans : - -दूध का खट्टा होना,खाने की ब्रेड का बनना,गीले आटे का खट्टा होना
13.: - निम्न में से कौन-सा आहार मानव शरीर में नये ऊतकों की वृद्धि के लिए पोषक तत्व प्रदान करता है?
Ans : - पनीर
14.: - निम्न में से कौन एक उड़ने वाली छिपकली है?
Ans : - ड्रेको

Ans : - किंग कोबरा
16.: - भारत में पायी जाने वाली सबसे बड़ी मछली कौन-सी है?
Ans : - ह्वेल शार्क
17.: - दालें किसका एक अच्छा स्रोत होती हैं?
Ans : - प्रोटीन
18.: - देशी घी में से सुगन्ध क्यों आती है?
Ans : - डाइएसिटिल के कारण
19.: - इन्द्रधनुष में किस रंग का विक्षेपण अधिक होता है?

Ans : - जे. एल. बेयर्ड

22.: - ‘गोबर गैस’ में मुख्य रूप से क्या पाया जाता है।
Ans : - मिथेन
23.: - दूध की शुद्धता का मापन किस यन्त्र से किया जाता है?

24.: - पृथ्वी पर सबसे अधिक मात्रा में पाया जाने वाला धातु तत्त्व कौन-सा है?

27.: - किस प्रकार के ऊतक शरीर के सुरक्षा कवच का कार्य करते हैं?
Ans : - एपिथीलियम ऊतक
28.: - मनुष्य ने सर्वप्रथम किस जन्तु को अपना पालतू बनाया?

40.: - ‘विटामिन-सी’ का सबसे अच्छा स्त्रोत क्या है?
Ans : - आंवला
  ☄भारतीय संविधान - प्रश्नोत्तर☄


प्रश्‍न 1- भारतीय संविधान सभा की प्रथम बैठक कब हुई । 
उत्‍तर - 9 दिसम्‍बर 1946 । 
प्रश्‍न 2- स‍ंविधान सभा का स्‍थाई अध्‍यक्ष कौन था । 
उत्‍तर - डॉ. राजेंन्‍द्र प्रसाद । 
प्रश्‍न 3- संविधान सभा का अस्‍थाई अध्‍यक्ष कौन था । 
उत्‍तर - डॉ. सच्चिदानंद सिन्‍हा । 
प्रश्‍न 4- संविधान सभा की प्रारूप समिति के अध्‍यक्ष कौन थे । 
उत्‍तर - डॉ. भीमराव अम्‍बेडकर । 
प्रश्‍न 5- संविधान सभा का औपचारिक रूप से प्रतिपादन किसने किया । 
उत्‍तर - एम. एन. राय । 
प्रश्‍न 6- भारत में संविधान सभा गठित करने का आधार क्‍या था । 
उत्‍तर - कैबिनेट मिशन योजना (1946) । 
प्रश्‍न 7- संविधान के गठन की मांग सर्वप्रथम 1895 में किस व्‍यक्ति ने की । 
उत्‍तर - बाल गंगाधर तिलक । 
प्रश्‍न 8- संविधान सभा में देशी रियासतों के कितने प्रतिनिधि थे । 
उत्‍तर - 70 । 
प्रश्‍न 9- संविधान सभा में किस देशी रियासत के प्रतिनिधि ने भाग नही लिया । 
उत्‍तर - हैदराबाद । 
प्रश्‍न 10- बी. आर. अम्‍बेडकर कहॉं के संविधान सभा में निर्वाचित हुए । 
उत्‍तर - बंगाल से । 
प्रश्‍न 11- संविधान सभा का संवैधानिक सलाहकार किसे नियुक्‍त किया गया था । 
उत्‍तर - बी. एन. राव । 
प्रश्‍न 12- संविधान सभा की प्रारूप समिति का गठन कब हुआ । 
उत्‍तर - 29 अगस्‍त 1947 । 
प्रश्‍न 13- संविधान की प्रारूप समिति के समक्ष प्रस्‍तावना का प्रस्‍ताव किसने रखा । 
उत्‍तर - जवाहर लाल नेहरू । 
प्रश्‍न 14- संविधान सभा की रचना हेतु संविधान का विचार सर्वप्रथम किसने प्रस्‍तुत किया । 
उत्‍तर - स्‍वराज पार्टी ने 1924 में । 
प्रश्‍न 15- संविधान सभा में भारत के संविधान को कब स्‍वीकृत किया । 
उत्‍तर - 26 नवम्‍बर 1946 । 
प्रश्‍न 16- संविधान को बनाने में कितना समय लगा । 
उत्‍तर - 2 वर्ष 11 माह 18 दिन । 
प्रश्‍न 17- स‍ंविधान में कितने अनुच्‍छेद है। 
उत्‍तर - 444 । 
प्रश्‍न 18- संविधान में कितने अध्‍याय है। 
उत्‍तर - 22 । 
प्रश्‍न 19- भारतीय सभा में कितनी अनुसूचियॉ है। 
उत्‍तर - 12 । 
प्रश्‍न 20- संविधान सभा का चुनाव किस आधार पर हुआ । 
उत्‍तर - वर्गीय मताधिकार पर ।*महत्वपूर्ण फॉर्मूले एवं जानकारियां*

Ans : - -ऊर्जा

Ans : - -ऑक्ज़ैलिक अम्ल
4.: - गन्ने में ‘लाल सड़न रोग’ किसके कारण उत्पन्न होता है?
Ans : - कवकों द्वारा
5.: - टेलीविजन का आविष्कार किसने किया था?
Ans : - जे. एल. बेयर्ड
6.: - किस प्रकार के ऊतक शरीर के सुरक्षा कवच का कार्य करते हैं?
Ans : - एपिथीलियम ऊतक
7.: - मनुष्य ने सर्वप्रथम किस जन्तु को अपना पालतू बनाया?
Ans : - कुत्ता
8.: - किस वैज्ञानिक ने सर्वप्रथम बर्फ़ के दो टुकड़ों को आपस में घिसकर पिघला दिया?
Ans : - डेवी
9: - हीरा चमकदार क्यों दिखाई देता है?
Ans : - सामूहिक आंतरिक परावर्तन के कारण
10.: - ‘गोबर गैस’ में मुख्य रूप से क्या पाया जाता है।
Ans : - मिथेन
11.: - निम्न में से कौन-सा आहार मानव शरीर में नये ऊतकों की वृद्धि के लिए पोषक तत्व प्रदान करता है?
Ans : - पनीर
12.: - निम्न में से कौन एक उड़ने वाली छिपकली है?
Ans : - ड्रेको

Ans : - टार्टरिक अम्ल
14.: - कैंसर सम्बन्धी रोगों का अध्ययन कहलाता है
Ans : - oncology
15.: - घोंसला बनाने वाला एकमात्र साँप कौन-सा है?
Ans : - किंग कोबरा
16.: - भारत में पायी जाने वाली सबसे बड़ी मछली कौन-सी है?
Ans : - ह्वेल शार्क
17.: - दालें किसका एक अच्छा स्रोत होती हैं?
Ans : - प्रोटीन

Ans : - डाइएसिटिल के कारण

Ans : - 7

Ans : - शोल्स

Ans : - ऐसीटम

Ans : - लैक्टोमीटर
24.: - पृथ्वी पर सबसे अधिक मात्रा में पाया जाने वाला धातु तत्त्व कौन-सा है?
Ans : - ऐलुमिनियम

Ans : - मेंगीफ़ेरा इण्डिका

Ans : - -जड़ों से

38.: - किण्वन का उदाहरण है

 *भौतिक राशि Physical quantities अन्य भौतिक राशियों से संबंध* 

1. क्षेत्रफल Area लंबाई × चौड़ाई

2. आयतन Volume लंबाई× चौड़ाई×ऊंचाई

3. द्रव्यमान घनत्व Density द्रव्यमान/आय
4. आवृत्ति Frequency 1/आवर्तकाल

5. वेग Velocity विस्थापन/समय

6. चाल Speed दूरी/समय

7. त्वरण Acceleration वेग/समय

8. बल Force द्रव्यमान × त्वरण

9. आवेग Impulse बल × समय

10. कार्य Work बल × दूरी

11. ऊर्जा Energy बल × दूरी

12. शक्ति Power कार्य/समय

13. संवेग Momentum द्रव्यमान × वेग

14. दाब Pressure बल/क्षेत्रफल

15. प्रतिबल Stress बल/क्षेत्रफल

16. विकृति Strain विमा में परिवर्तन/मूल विमा

17. प्रत्यास्थता गुणांक Coefficient of elasticity प्रतिबल/विकृति

18. पृष्ठ तनाव Surface tension बल/लंबाई

19. पृष्ठ ऊर्जा Surface energy ऊर्जा/क्षेत्रफल

20. वेग प्रवणता Velocity gradient वेग/दूरी

21. दाब प्रवणता Pressure gradient दाब/दूरी

22. श्यानता गुणांक Coefficient of viscosity बल/(क्षेत्रफल× वेग प्रवणता)

23. कोण Angel चाप/त्रिज्या

24. त्रिकोणमितीय अनुपात Trigonometric ratio लंबाई/लंबाई

25. कोणीय वेग Angular velocity कोण/समय

26. कोणीय त्वरण Angular acelleration कोणीय वेग/समय

27. कोणीय संवेग Angular momentum जड़त्व आघूर्ण × कोणीय वेग

28. जड़त्व आघूर्ण Moment of inertia द्रव्यमान× (परिभ्रमण त्रिज्या)2

29. बल आघूर्ण Torque बल × दूरी

30. कोणीय आवृत्ति Angular frequency 2π × आवृत्ति

31. गुरुत्वीय सार्वत्रिक नियतांक Universal constant of gravity बल× (दूरी)2/(द्रव्यमान)2

32. प्लांक नियतांक Plank’s constant ऊर्जा/आवृत्ति

33. विशिष्ट उष्मा Specific heat उष्मीय ऊर्जा/(द्रव्यमान× ताप)

34. उष्मा धारिता Heat capacity ऊष्मीय ऊर्जा/ताप

35. बोल्टजमान नियतांक Boltzmann’s constant ऊर्जा/ताप

36. स्टीफन नियतांक Stefan’s constant (ऊर्जा/क्षेत्रफल× समय)/(ताप)4

37. गैस नियतांक Gas constant (दाब× आयतन)/(मोल× ताप )

38. आवेश Charge विद्युत धारा × समय

39. विभवातंर Potential difference कार्य/आवेश

40. प्रतिरोध Resistance विभवांतर/विद्युत धारा

41. धारिता Capacity आवेश/विभवांतर

42. विद्युत क्षेत्र Electric field वैद्युत बल/आवेश

43. चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र Magnetic field बल/(विद्युत धारा× लंबाई)

44. चुम्बकीय फ्लक्स Magnetic flux चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र × लंबाई

45. प्रेरकत्व Inductance चुम्बकीय फ्लक्स/विद्युत धारा

46. वीन नियतांक Wein’s constant तरंगदैर्ध्य ×ताप

47. चालकता Conductivity 1/प्रतिरोध

48. एंट्रॅापी Entropy ऊष्मीय ऊर्जा / ताप

49. गुप्त उष्मा Latent heat उष्मीय ऊर्जा / द्रव्यमान

50. तापीय प्रसार गुणांक Coefficient of thermal expansion विमा में परिवर्तन / (मूल विमा × ताप )

nbsp51. आयतन प्रत्यास्थता गुणांक Bulk modulus ( आयतन × दाब में परिवर्तन )/आयतन में परिवर्तन

52. वैद्युत प्रतिरोधकता Electric resistance ( प्रतिरोध × क्षेत्रफल )/ लंबाई

53. वैद्युत द्विध्रुव आघूर्ण Electric dipole moment बल आघूर्ण / विद्युत क्षेत्र

54. चुम्बकीय द्विध्रुव आघूर्ण Magnetic dipole moment बल आघूर्ण / चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र

55. चुम्बकीय क्षेत्र प्रबलता चुम्बकीय आघूर्ण / आयतन

56. अपवर्तनांक Refractive index निर्वात में प्रकाश की चाल/माध्यम में प्रकाश की चाल

57. तरंग संख्या Wave number 2π / तरंगदैर्ध्य

58. विकिरण शक्ति Radiant power उत्सर्जित ऊर्जा / समय

59. विकिरण तीव्रता Radiant intensity विकिरण शक्ति / घन कोण

60. हबल नियतांक Hubble constant पश्च सरण चाल /दूरी

  ☄भारतीय संविधान - प्रश्नोत्तर☄


प्रश्‍न 1- भारतीय संविधान सभा की प्रथम बैठक कब हुई । 
उत्‍तर - 9 दिसम्‍बर 1946 । 
प्रश्‍न 2- स‍ंविधान सभा का स्‍थाई अध्‍यक्ष कौन था । 
उत्‍तर - डॉ. राजेंन्‍द्र प्रसाद । 
प्रश्‍न 3- संविधान सभा का अस्‍थाई अध्‍यक्ष कौन था । 
उत्‍तर - डॉ. सच्चिदानंद सिन्‍हा । 
प्रश्‍न 4- संविधान सभा की प्रारूप समिति के अध्‍यक्ष कौन थे । 
उत्‍तर - डॉ. भीमराव अम्‍बेडकर । 
प्रश्‍न 5- संविधान सभा का औपचारिक रूप से प्रतिपादन किसने किया । 
उत्‍तर - एम. एन. राय । 
प्रश्‍न 6- भारत में संविधान सभा गठित करने का आधार क्‍या था । 
उत्‍तर - कैबिनेट मिशन योजना (1946) । 
प्रश्‍न 7- संविधान के गठन की मांग सर्वप्रथम 1895 में किस व्‍यक्ति ने की । 
उत्‍तर - बाल गंगाधर तिलक । 
प्रश्‍न 8- संविधान सभा में देशी रियासतों के कितने प्रतिनिधि थे । 
उत्‍तर - 70 । 
प्रश्‍न 9- संविधान सभा में किस देशी रियासत के प्रतिनिधि ने भाग नही लिया । 
उत्‍तर - हैदराबाद । 
प्रश्‍न 10- बी. आर. अम्‍बेडकर कहॉं के संविधान सभा में निर्वाचित हुए । 
उत्‍तर - बंगाल से । 
प्रश्‍न 11- संविधान सभा का संवैधानिक सलाहकार किसे नियुक्‍त किया गया था । 
उत्‍तर - बी. एन. राव । 
प्रश्‍न 12- संविधान सभा की प्रारूप समिति का गठन कब हुआ । 
उत्‍तर - 29 अगस्‍त 1947 । 
प्रश्‍न 13- संविधान की प्रारूप समिति के समक्ष प्रस्‍तावना का प्रस्‍ताव किसने रखा । 
उत्‍तर - जवाहर लाल नेहरू । 
प्रश्‍न 14- संविधान सभा की रचना हेतु संविधान का विचार सर्वप्रथम किसने प्रस्‍तुत किया । 
उत्‍तर - स्‍वराज पार्टी ने 1924 में । 
प्रश्‍न 15- संविधान सभा में भारत के संविधान को कब स्‍वीकृत किया । 
उत्‍तर - 26 नवम्‍बर 1946 । 
प्रश्‍न 16- संविधान को बनाने में कितना समय लगा । 
उत्‍तर - 2 वर्ष 11 माह 18 दिन । 
प्रश्‍न 17- स‍ंविधान में कितने अनुच्‍छेद है। 
उत्‍तर - 444 । 
प्रश्‍न 18- संविधान में कितने अध्‍याय है। 
उत्‍तर - 22 । 
प्रश्‍न 19- भारतीय सभा में कितनी अनुसूचियॉ है। 
उत्‍तर - 12 । 
प्रश्‍न 20- संविधान सभा का चुनाव किस आधार पर हुआ । 
उत्‍तर - वर्गीय मताधिकार पर ।
आपसे निवेदन है की ये मैसेज सभी छात्रो तक पहुँचाऐ
1. (α+в)²= α²+2αв+в²
2. (α+в)²= (α-в)²+4αв
3. (α-в)²= α²-2αв+в²
4. (α-в)²= (α+в)²-4αв
5. α² + в²= (α+в)² - 2αв.
6. α² + в²= (α-в)² + 2αв.
7. α²-в² =(α + в)(α - в)
8. 2(α² + в²) = (α+ в)² + (α - в)²
9. 4αв = (α + в)² -(α-в)²
10. αв ={(α+в)/2}²-{(α-в)/2}²
11. (α + в + ¢)² = α² + в² + ¢² + 2(αв + в¢ + ¢α)
12. (α + в)³ = α³ + 3α²в + 3αв² + в³
13. (α + в)³ = α³ + в³ + 3αв(α + в)
14. (α-в)³=α³-3α²в+3αв²-в³
15. α³ + в³ = (α + в) (α² -αв + в²)
16. α³ + в³ = (α+ в)³ -3αв(α+ в)
17. α³ -в³ = (α -в) (α² + αв + в²)
18. α³ -в³ = (α-в)³ + 3αв(α-в)

1. युधिष्ठिर    2. भीम    3. अर्जुन
4. नकुल।      5. सहदेव

( इन पांचों के अलावा , महाबली कर्ण भी कुंती के ही पुत्र थे , परन्तु उनकी गिनती पांडवों में नहीं की जाती है )

यहाँ ध्यान रखें कि… पाण्डु के उपरोक्त पाँचों पुत्रों में से युधिष्ठिर, भीम और अर्जुन
की माता कुन्ती थीं ……तथा , नकुल और सहदेव की माता माद्री थी ।

वहीँ …. धृतराष्ट्र और गांधारी के सौ पुत्र…..

100. युयुत्सु

( इन 100 भाइयों के अलावा कौरवों की एक बहनभी थी… जिसका नाम""दुशाला""था,
जिसका विवाह"जयद्रथ"सेहुआ था )

"श्री मद्-भगवत गीता"के बारे में-

ॐ . किसको किसने सुनाई?
उ.- श्रीकृष्ण ने अर्जुन को सुनाई। 

ॐ . कब सुनाई?
उ.- आज से  5700 साल पहले सुनाई।

ॐ. भगवान ने किस दिन गीता सुनाई?
उ.- रविवार के दिन।

ॐ. कोनसी तिथि को?
उ.- एकादशी 

ॐ. कहा सुनाई?
उ.- कुरुक्षेत्र की रणभूमि में।

ॐ. कितनी देर में सुनाई?
उ.- लगभग 45 मिनट में

ॐ. क्यू सुनाई?
उ.- कर्त्तव्य से भटके हुए अर्जुन को कर्त्तव्य सिखाने के लिए और आने वाली पीढियों को धर्म-ज्ञान सिखाने के लिए।

ॐ. कितने अध्याय है?
उ.- कुल 18 अध्याय

ॐ. कितने श्लोक है?
उ.- 700 श्लोक

ॐ. गीता में क्या-क्या बताया गया है?
उ.- ज्ञान-भक्ति-कर्म योग मार्गो की विस्तृत व्याख्या की गयी है, इन मार्गो पर चलने से व्यक्ति निश्चित ही परमपद का अधिकारी बन जाता है। 

ॐ. गीता को अर्जुन के अलावा 
और किन किन लोगो ने सुना?
उ.- धृतराष्ट्र एवं संजय ने

ॐ. अर्जुन से पहले गीता का पावन ज्ञान किन्हें मिला था?
उ.- भगवान सूर्यदेव को

ॐ. गीता की गिनती किन धर्म-ग्रंथो में आती है?
उ.- उपनिषदों में

ॐ. गीता किस महाग्रंथ का भाग है....?
उ.- गीता महाभारत के एक अध्याय शांति-पर्व का एक हिस्सा है।

ॐ. गीता का दूसरा नाम क्या है?
उ.- गीतोपनिषद

ॐ. गीता का सार क्या है?
उ.- प्रभु श्रीकृष्ण की शरण लेना

ॐ. गीता में किसने कितने श्लोक कहे है?
उ.- श्रीकृष्ण जी ने- 574
अर्जुन ने- 85 
धृतराष्ट्र ने- 1
संजय ने- 40.

अपनी युवा-पीढ़ी को गीता जी के बारे में जानकारी पहुचाने हेतु इसे ज्यादा से ज्यादा शेअर करे। धन्यवाद

अधूरा ज्ञान खतरना होता है।

33 करोड नहीँ  33 कोटी देवी देवता हैँ हिँदू
धर्म मेँ।

कोटि = प्रकार। 
देवभाषा संस्कृत में कोटि के दो अर्थ होते है,

कोटि का मतलब प्रकार होता है और एक अर्थ करोड़ भी होता।

हिन्दू धर्म का दुष्प्रचार करने के लिए ये बात उडाई गयी की हिन्दुओ के 33 करोड़ देवी देवता हैं और अब तो मुर्ख हिन्दू खुद ही गाते फिरते हैं की हमारे 33 करोड़ देवी देवता हैं...

कुल 33 प्रकार के देवी देवता हैँ हिँदू धर्म मे :-

12 प्रकार हैँ
आदित्य , धाता, मित, आर्यमा,
शक्रा, वरुण, अँश, भाग, विवास्वान, पूष,
सविता, तवास्था, और विष्णु...!

8 प्रकार हे :-
वासु:, धर, ध्रुव, सोम, अह, अनिल, अनल, प्रत्युष और प्रभाष।

11 प्रकार है :- 
रुद्र: ,हर,बहुरुप, त्रयँबक,
अपराजिता, बृषाकापि, शँभू, कपार्दी,
रेवात, मृगव्याध, शर्वा, और कपाली।

एवँ
दो प्रकार हैँ अश्विनी और कुमार।

कुल :- 12+8+11+2=33 कोटी 

अगर कभी भगवान् के आगे हाथ जोड़ा है
तो इस जानकारी को अधिक से अधिक
लोगो तक पहुचाएं। ।

🙏🙏🙏🙏🙏🙏🙏🙏🙏
१ हिन्दु हाेने के नाते जानना ज़रूरी है

This is very good information for all of us ... जय श्रीकृष्ण ...

अब आपकी बारी है कि इस जानकारी को आगे बढ़ाएँ ......

24/11/21, 18:31 - +91 78150 75501: Dear class members, it is to remind you all that the online exam of SYSTEM MODELLING AND DESIGN LAB (EC2705) for EC students will be conducted on 25.11.2021 (Thursday) over MS team, starting at 1:00 PM. The modalities for the online exam are as follows:


	
The online exam will be conducted in three teams: System Mod. & Des. Lab S2 with TA as Mrs. Sanjana Sahoo, System Mod. & Des. Lab S201 with TA as Ms. Anuradha Verma, and System Mod. & Des. Lab.S202 with TA as Mr. Mohammad Ali. Subsequently, the class members will be distributed among these teams and will be notified when added.
	
The online exam duration will be of two hours.
	
The online exam will be divided into four parts.
	
In the first part, the class members have to appear a lab test which will be conducted in Microsoft forms. You are required to perform the experiment assigned to you in the Microsoft form and make a word document of the experiment with sections such as objective of the experiment, software required, MATLAB code, results and discussions (include figures), and conclusion. You can upload your response in pdf file format.
	
In the second part, the class members have to appear for a lab quiz which will be conducted in Microsoft forms. You are requested to write answers to each question on A4 size white paper with your name, roll number, and page number at the top right corner of each and every page of A4 size white paper. You can upload your response in pdf file format (scanned properly).
	
In the third part, the class members have to appear for viva voice which will be conducted over MS team calls. The TA in each team will make a call directly to their respective class members.
	
In the fourth part, the class members have to submit their lab record files in Microsoft forms. You are required to upload the lab record file in pdf format.
	
During the examination period, the class members are advised to turn on MS teams video, to ensure their visibility to invigilators.
	
The class members should verify their responses before clicking the final submit button. Only one form can be submitted by one student.
	
Further instructions and help on online exam will be provided to the class members in the teams by their respective TA's.

24/11/21, 19:10 - Jyoti EI NITR: Dear class members, it is to remind you all that the online exam of SYSTEM MODELLING AND DESIGN LAB (EC2705) for EIE students will be conducted on 26.11.2021 (Friday) over MS team, starting at 1:00 PM. The modalities for the online exam are as follows: The online exam will be conducted in three teams: System Mod. & Des. Lab S101 with TA as Mrs. Sanjana Sahoo, System Mod. & Des. Lab S1 with TA as Ms. Anuradha Verma, and System Mod. & Des. Lab.S02 with TA as Mr. Mohammad Ali. Subsequently, the class members will be distributed among these teams and will be notified when added. The online exam duration will be of two hours. The online exam will be divided into four parts. In the first part, the class members have to appear a lab test which will be conducted in Microsoft forms. You are required to perform the experiment assigned to you in the Microsoft form and make a word document of the experiment with sections such as objective of the experiment, software required, MATLAB code, results and discussions (include figures), and conclusion. You can upload your response in pdf file format. In the second part, the class members have to appear for a lab quiz which will be conducted in Microsoft forms. You are requested to write answers to each question on A4 size white paper(subjective in nature) with your name, roll number, and page number at the top right corner of each and every page of A4 size white paper. You can upload your response in pdf file format (scanned properly). In the third part, the class members have to appear for viva voice which will be conducted over MS team calls. The TA in each team will make a call(video) directly to their respective class members. In the fourth part, the class members have to submit their lab record files in Microsoft forms. You are required to upload the lab record file in pdf format. During the examination period, the class members are advised to turn on MS teams video, to ensure their visibility to invigilators. The class members should verify their responses before clicking the final submit button. Only one form can be submitted by one student. Further instructions and help for online exam will be provided to the class members in the teams by their respective TA's.

10/12/21, 10:28 - +91 80581 59773: *Answer 14* 

 1. *The Product Method:* 
In this method, all goods and services produced during the year in various industries are added up. This is also known as value-added to GDP or GDP at the sector of origin's cost factor. India includes the following items: agriculture and allied services; mining; development, construction, the supply of electricity, gas, and water, transport, communication, and trade; banking and insurance; real estate and property ownership of residential and commercial services and public administration and defence and other services (or government services). It is, in other words, the amount of the added gross value.

2. *Expenditure Method* :
This approach focuses on products and services generated during one year within the region.

GDP is subtracted from the portion of consumption, investment, and government spending expended on imports. Likewise, all manufactured components, such as raw materials used in the manufacture of products for sale, are also exempt.

Thus GDP by expenditure method at market prices is net export, which can be positive or negative.

*The 5th National Engineering Olympiad*!

The National Engineering Olympiad is a competitive platform for the engineering students to showcase your aptitude skills and represent yourself at the national level.

Register now!
https://nationalolympiad.org/?refid=341871812

*The Rounds:*
Similar to the previous four editions of the National Engineering Olympiad, the exam will be conducted in two rounds.

Round 1: Basic Aptitude Test- 60 mins, 60 questions. 
Dates are 18th & 19th December 2021. 
Round 2: Technical Ability Test- Online MCQ Exam based on your syllabus of the year & branch you are studying in. 

*Please Note:*
Both rounds are to be attempted _online_ from your home!

*The Rewards:* 

_For the top performers:_
-Top 10 of each year & branch will be awarded a Medal of Excellence.
-Top 30 of each year & branch will be awarded a Certificate of Excellence.

_For all participants:_
-Guaranteed Internships in various domains.
-A national-level participation certificate.
-Career-oriented webinars by experts for free.

(More details are available on the website)

Hurry up! Last day to register for Phase 3 is 17th December.
Visit https://nationalolympiad.org/?refid=341871812

25/02/22, 09:19 - Sarada Prasad Panda Nitrkl: The procedure for the population to be notified of the threat of occurrence military emergency:
If you hear the continuous operation of sirens for a long time
(more than 3 minutes) - this means an alarm signal - "Attention everyone!".
If you are in an apartment and have received information about possible shelling:
• You must leave the room as soon as possible.
• If there is a basement - go down to the basement. If there is no basement - go down to lower floors. The lower the better. Ideally - all on the first floor.
• You need to go into the inner room, the more concrete around, the better (find load-bearing walls), you can use the bathroom or toilet, vestibules, pantries. Windows can be equipped with sofa cushions (large, dense, but better with sandbags), cover with solid furniture, but not empty.
• If all rooms are outside - go to the stairwell.
Never be near windows!
In addition to basements you can hide:
• In the underpass; metro stations.
Don't panic! You may think it's easy to say, but it's worth a try do. Occupy your psyche with something. It can be considered an explosion: know the maximum after 100 explosions the shelling will end for sure. You can try to mentally count minutes. First, it's distracting. Secondly, so you can navigate the situation: artillery fire does not last forever, maximum - twenty minutes air raid - much less.
After the shelling (bombing): do not rush to leave the shelter. Single shots are possible. Leaving place of refuge, do not rush to relax. Now all your attention should be concentrated at your feet! Do not pick up any strangers from the ground items: an air bomb, a rocket or a projectile could be a cluster!
Warheads often break when dropped, but can explode later,
in the hands - from the slightest movement or touch.
All attention is paid to teenagers: do not let them lift anything from under their feet!
In the case of a decision on the partial evacuation of certain categories of citizens, await notification of the local government's determination of evacuation teams points. Have an anxious suitcase with you: passport, suitcase (backpack) with clothes for the season, necessary medicines, money, valuables, food and water for several days.
During the evacuation it is necessary:
- comply with all orders of evacuation officials;
- adhere to discipline and order on the route of movement, on transport and in settlement area at the new location;
- upon arrival at the final evacuation point, register;
- to assist public order protection bodies and medical workers;
- if necessary, provide assistance to sick people.

03/03/22, 08:41 - Pramod Goyal EI Nit R: 1.What is balanced & unbalanced load in a three phase system?
Ans. In a balanced three-phase system, the phase voltages should be equal or very close to equal. Unbalance or imbalance is a measurement of the inequality of the phase voltages. Voltage imbalance is the measure of voltage differences between the phases of a three-phase system. It degrades the performance and shortens the life of three-phase motors.
2. Explain how you will find the multiplying factor of the watt meter.
Ans. The Multiplication Factor (MF) is: MF = (voltage range x current range x power factor)/(range of the wattmeter scale
3. Verify theoretically how the two wattmeter method gives the power measurement under both balanced and unbalanced condition
Ans. Yeh fuck off
4.What is line & phase voltage in three phase system?
Ans. Line voltage is the voltage measured between any two lines in a three-phase circuit. Phase voltage is the voltage measured across a single component in a three-phase source or load.
5. What is the difference between star & delta connection in 3 phase system
Ans. In STAR Connection, the starting or finishing ends (similar ends) of three coils are connected together to form the neutral point. A common wire is taken out from the neutral point which is called Neutral. In DELTA Connection, the opposite ends of three coils are connected together.

03/03/22, 08:49 - Goutam EI Nitr: Why does wattmeter gives negative reading sometimes while measuring 3 phase unbalanced load?
03/03/22, 08:49 - Goutam EI Nitr: The reading of a wattmeter is proportional to (current thro' the current coil)x(voltage across the pressure coil)xCosine(angle between this current and this voltage). So if this angle becomes more than 90 degrees the the reading of the wattmeter will be negative.This could happen in a 3-ph unbalanced circuit. For a 3-ph balanced load the two wattmeter readings will be,say Vab*Ia*cos (30+phi) and Vcb*Ic* cos(30-phi). So if phi >60 degrees (pf less than 0.5) a negative reading is obtained.

03/03/22, 12:22 - +91 82994 36752: To
The Director,
National Institute of Technology, Rourkela, Odisha

XX March 2022
Subject : Request to review the decision regarding resumption of offline classes

Respected Sir,

With reference to Circular number NITR/RG/2002/0104 dated 02.03.2022, I am writing this letter to draw your attention to the problems we, students of NITR are facing. Although the current scenario of COVID-19 is not as dire as before, resuming of offline classes in this short span of time is still a hectic and difficult process for us students. The multiple problems faced by us are:

•	The sudden notice for resumption of offline classes would create a sudden inflow of students in large numbers which combined with the no-quarantine decision might lead to another COVID outbreak in the campus, putting all of our health and lives at risk.

•	Continuous online classes and exams for a prolonged period of time has become a part of our schedule and lives and changing it suddenly to another mode is going to be tedious and mentally straining.

•	The grades for the final exams affect our CG by 50% and hence it is unreasonable to suddenly ask us to give the exam whilst adjusting to the change in surrounding and all other pressures for which we are unprepared.

•	Adjusting to the new environment we will suddenly be facing in the campus, as well as the time-zone adjustment is sure to take a toll on us, resulting us to divert our focus from studies.

•	In case of foreign students, parents are worried about the short notice as it is not feasible for us to book flights this soon and travel overseas as there are still flight restrictions between countries and the costs are extremely high because of lack of availability of flights. Some of us have our VISA renewals soon and might have to wait for it to be processed as our Passports are still with the respective authorities.

Taking all these issues into consideration, resumption of classes after this semester ends or during the summer break would be preferable and would give us ample amount of time to settle down and solve our problems such as adapting to new environment and time zones, getting used to the new mode and taking necessary precautions such as quarantine which ensures our safety without much stress, panic and tension which would also be a relief for our parents. It would be highly appreciated if the administration could take these issues into consideration and take action accordingly. Your response shall be much awaited. 

Yours Sincerely,

Date: 16.03.2022

 

N O T I C E

SUB- Verificationof Original certificates/documents for all UG (B.Tech., B.Arch., Dual Degree., Int.M.Sc)Students admitted during the academic year 2020-21
 

 

This is for theinformation of all 2nd-year students of the UG programmes (B.Tech.,B.Arch.,Dual Degree., Int.M.Sc) admittedduring the academic year 2020-21, that their admission process was purely provisional subject to verification of theoriginal documents during physical reporting to the institute. As per institute rules, confirmation of theadmission and further continuance in the academic programme is subjectto physical verification of original certificates/documentsand submission of three certificates in original. viz. Conduct Certificate, College Leaving Certificate/Transfer Certificate,Migration Certificate, and Valid JEE Main Score card.They have tosubmit self-attested photocopies of other certificates/mark sheets alongwith the originals marksheets/cerificates/documents as listedbelow for verification.

 

1.    10thMark Sheet &Certificate(Original with photocopy)

2.    12thMark Sheet &Certificate(Original with photocopy)

3.    CollegeLeaving/Transfer Certificate(Original )

4.    MigrationCertificate(Original)

5.    ConductCertificate(Original)

6.    CasteCertificate(Original with photocopy)

7.    PWDCertificate(if) (Original with photocopy)

8.    JEEmain Rank Card(coloured printout)

9.    ThreePassport size coloured photographs

As per the Circular No-NITR/RG2022/M/0104, dated 2nd march2022,you were instructed to return to the Institute campus by 23rdmarch 2022.Therefore, you are advised to carry theoriginal copies of your marksheet/certificates/reservation certificates/other documents as applicable, with you for physical verification at the Institute.The exact date/schedule for  the document verificationwill be notified shortly.

For any queries, please contact:

This is issued with the approval ofthe competent authority.

24/03/22, 09:05 - +91 83742 25936: What is Energy Meter?
                Device that measure the amount of energy consumed by a equipment.
Aim of the Experiment?
 Test Energy meter at different power factors 0.5, 0.866, 1 without connecting any capacitive or inductive load

Specification of  Single phase energy meter is 230V, 5A, 1500 RPU
Phase difference between R and B phase is 240 degrees.
The Pressure coil of energy meter always take voltage from R phase only
Current coil has provision to take current from both R and B phase Simultaneously or individually.

31/03/22, 09:20 - +91 70609 05001: No:NITR/AC/UG&PG/2022/M/197                                                                    

Date: 30.03.2022

N O T I C E

*Subject: Payment of Spring Semester (2021-22) Fees-reg*

Reference: Notice no. NITR/AC/UG&PG/2022/M/153,  dated 16.03.2022, issued from the Academic(UG&PG) office.

 

Dear Students,

The payment portal for Spring Semester (2021-22) Fees forthe students across all UG, PG, & researchprogrammes (including all first-year students of UG, PG, &Research programmes admitted in Autumn 2021-22), is functional now. The students can make the payment by visiting the followinglink;

 

https://www.onlinesbi.com/sbicollect/icollecthome.htm?corpID=1509159

Steps to Follow:

1.     Enter the above address in the browser and click the Check Boxto acceptterms & conditions and clickon the “proceed” button.

2.      SelectPayment Category – “SPRING SEMESTER FEE 2021-22”

3.      Now enterroll no. in CAPITALLETTER and Click on SUBMITButton.

4.      Fillin your Name,DOB, Mobile, E-Mail (Optional),and Textshown and click Submit.

5.      Onthe next page, check all details and confirm. It will lead to the Payment page.

6.      Choosethe paymentoption available and make the payment.

Please Note: The fee payment portal will remain open till 11th April 2022

Students who fail tomake payment within the scheduled dates shall be liable to pay a late fine ofRs. 1000.00, which will be added to the next semester’s demand.

Important points to note:

a.         While making the payment, if the transaction gets failedthen please bring the same to the notice of the academic office with a screenshotimmediately. Please note down the transaction reference number, which will behelpful to track the details.

b.         Please ensure a good and stable internet speed while makingthe payment to avoid interruption.

c.         All foreign students (DASA/CIWG/COMPEX/Studyin India schemes/Other foreign schemes) are suggested to please check the fee details beforemaking the payment. If you find any discrepancy, bring the same to the noticeof the academic office by contacting the help desk within the designatedschedule.

d.        If there is any short payment due to calculation erroror non-availability of value from any source, it has to be paid by theconcerned student whenever it is brought to the notice of the concerned student.

e.         If any excess amount is paid by the student it will beadjusted in the next semester fee or while taking clearance from the instituteafter graduation.

f.          No request for achange of income category for the academic year 2021-22 or the precedingyears/semesters will be entertained at this stage. The students who have uploadedvalid documents for the academic year (2021-22) in the NITRIS portal as per thenotification have been granted the tuition fee waiver in compliance with the instituterules. Any change in the income group is impossible at this stage as thecategories are already incorporated & approved in the database, demand isgenerated, and the fee collection is LIVE.

g.         This is to furtherreiterate that the students of the 2021 admission batch (1st Year UG), whohave not physically returned to the campus willnot have to pay the mess dues till they physically return to the campus andoccupy their hostels. The mess advance paid by them at the time ofadmission (Autumn 2021-22) is like a standing advance for mess dues and the studenthas to pay the mess bill according to the actual consumption after return tothe campus. The above mess advance shall be adjusted against the final semestermess dues (at actuals) at the end of the academic programme and vacating thehostel. The balance mess advance (if any) shall be refunded back to thestudent.

h.         There are multiple queries regarding fee structure. Forthe convenience of all UG & PG students, the same (applicable for Indianstudents for AY:2021-22) is uploaded under the announcement section of ourinstitute website for reference. The PhD students may contact the Academic-researchoffice for their fee structure-related queries.

09/05/22, 20:18 - +91 78150 75501: No.NITR/AC/UG&PG/2021/M/0253                                                            

Date:05.05.2022

N O T I C E

Sub:  Submission of Family Income Certificate byB.Tech./B.Arch./Dual degree students availing Tuition Fee waiver benefit during the Academic year 2022-23 (Autumn & Springsemester)-reg.

This is for the information of thestudents studying in B. Tech. 1styear (2021 admission batch), 2ndyear (2020 admission batch), 3rd year (2019 admission batch); B.Arch./Dual Degree1st year (2021 admission batch), 2nd year(2020 admission batch), 3rd year (2019 admission batch), and 4th year (2018 admissionbatch), that the NITRIS portal is now activated(10th – 17th May 2022)for uploading their Family IncomeCertificate for the academicyear 2022-23.

 

Students of theFinal year Dual Degree programme (2018 admission batch) willing/eligible toavail the GATE scholarship/stipend are not eligible for the Tuition fee waiver.

The eligible studentswith total family income from all sources in the preceding the financial year 2021-22 (1st April 2021 to31st March 2022) below 1 Lakh/5 Lakhs [as the case maybe], and interested to avail TuitionFee waiver benefit for theAcademicyear 2022-23 (Autumn & Spring semester)are advised to upload valid Family Income Certificate of their parents mentioning “Total Family Income from all sources” issued for the preceding FinancialYear.

The certificate may be uploaded to theNITRIS portal at the given link: NITRIS à ACADEMIC à AcademicForms/Certificate à Income Certificate. It may please be noted that the portalwill be open for 8 days only i.e. from 10th May to 17th May2022 to upload the same and no further extension shall be granted beyond thescheduled date.

Those who have alreadysubmitted their family annual income certificate having validity for more than 1 year are also required to submit the Income Certificate/supporting affidavits or othertestimonials as applicable (Death certificate,divorce certificate etc.) againin the NITRIS Portal withinthe scheduled dates.
The concerned studentshould make one single PDF file [Father's & Mother's Income certificate & supporting affidavits or other testimonials as applicable (Death certificate, divorce certificate etc.)], mentioninghis/her Name & Roll Number, and upload it in the NITRIS portal.

Importantpoints to note;

1.     “Totalfamily income from all the sources” for the preceding financial year 2021- 22 must be mentioned in the income certificate.

2.     Anincome certificate should be issued in favour of the Parents mentioning thetotal Income of the family from all sources [Definition of the family should be mentioned in the certificate].

3.     Ifthe income certificate is issued in favour of either of the parents, anaffidavit in support of the other parent’s income must be submitted [forexample, if the father’s income certificate is submitted, an affidavit insupport of the mother’s income is required to be submitted along with thefather’s income certificate OR vice versa]. The affidavit should be signed by anappropriate authority, not below the rank of a Magistrate.

4.     Incase, either of the parents is deceased and the income certificate is issued infavour of the other parent, it shouldbe accompanied by the Death Certificate of the deceased parent.

5.     Anincome certificate should be issued by the competent authority of the concerned State. Sometimes it is seen that the income certificate is issued by theconcerned authority having validity for more than one year, but in the heading,it is mentioned as “valid for the financial year 2021-22 only”. Suchcertificates will be rejected. Onlythose certificates citing validity for the “the financial year 2022-23” will be accepted.

6.     Theincome of the family/parents should be specified/included for the previousfinancial year (the financialyear 2021-22; from 1st April 2021 to 31st March2022).

7.     The income certificate must be issued on or after 1st April 2022.

8.     Theincome certificate must comply with the above guidelines, failing which thesame shall be liable to be rejected. The student who fails to submitthe valid income certificate within the stipulated period will not be allowed afee waiver on a later date.

9.     Incase of any query/defect regarding the income, certificate is detected, thesame will be reverted (mentioning the reason) to the student for compliance. Ifthe student fails to comply within the stipulated period the certificate willbe rejected and no further claim regarding the same shall be entertained.Students are hereby advised to check their webmail regularly. No separate communicationshall be made in this regard.

10. Noother mode of income certificate submission other than the NITRIS portal willbe entertained and shall be summarily rejected. If anyone fails to submit thecertificate in the NITRIS within the scheduled period (i.e.before 17th May 2022) his/her claim for the tuition fee waiver for the academic year 2022-23shall be rejected/forfeited. NO FURTHER COMMUNICATION REGARDING THE SAME SHALL BE ENTERTAINED INFUTURE.

 

This is issued with the approval of thecompetent authority.

 

 
Sd/- 
Assistant Registrar (Academic-UG&PG),
Academic Office,

NIT Rourkela. 

For any further clarification, pleasecontact student help desk@ +91 6612462038 (1600 hrs to 1800 hrs)

Greetings from the NITR Placement Committee of 2022-23!

As we are about to welcome yet another academic year, the companies are going to flood in for recruiting students for *Full Time* and *Intern* roles.

https://forms.gle/UxZ6CSxrHQoCstiu7

*Deadline:*
11:59 pm
5th June, 2022

_Students not filling up the form won't be considered as eligible candidates for the Placement Season of 2022-23_

In case of any query, please reach out to your respective Branch Placement Coordinators.

*NOTE:* Fill the form carefully and adhere to one application per candidate. Multiple entries from the same candidate will account for severe actions. Also, data like CGPA and JEE score will be sent to academics for verification so ensure that you enter the correct details to avoid any action.

All the best!

12/07/22, 12:48 - Goutam EI Nitr: Dear Student Friends,

Greetings. I am happy to share with you all that from this semester onwards there will be no LAN port registrations for any students by Computer & Informatics Centre.

You will be able to access the Institute Internet from any Halls of Residence. So effectively there will not be any long Q's which used to be the normal practice every year. At the same time the freedom given to you all comes with greater responsibility such as;

1. Please do not connect any Wi-Fi routers since it will start distributing IP's via DHCP and choke the hostel network.

2. Please do not download anything which has a copyright and other issues.

I welcome you all back to the Institute and look forward to meeting you all soon.

Regards

Prof. Manish Okade
HoD, Computer & Informatics Centre
NIT Rourkela
